		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Jul 1st 7:35 PM2004 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=1088711989753732862&num=7&post=1&replyto=108872494162727110"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a> | <a class="sm" href="/db/journal2.html?user=362017"><img border="0" src="/shared/user_journal.gif" border="0" height="12" width="17" /> User's Journal</a>   <a name=108872494162727110></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=362017"><span id=Scholar>Lierta Defender of Justice</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />118 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Lierta&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Hey, your bard is on my server. <img border="0" src="/shared/smilies/smile.gif" /><br><br>Twisting songs is when you keep two or more songs playing simultaneously.&nbsp;&nbsp;To do this, you should first hotkey any songs you want to twist.  Hit the hotkey to start your first song; as soon as the casting bar disappears and the song is going, turn it off by hitting the hotkey for your second song.  Quickly start your next song; when it is finished casting, hit the hotkey to turn it off, and then start your first song again.  (So you should be hitting keys like this: 1,1,2,2,1,1,2,2, etc.)  If you continue in this manner, you should be able to keep those 2 songs playing at the same time, thus getting the effects of both songs.  You can practice this to learn to twist 3 or 4 songs.  (Hope that makes sense. :)<br><br>There are several different ways to solo a bard, most of which you can't do until the 20s and 30s.  Chant kiting involves twisting Selo's Accelerando song and some dot songs on a single mob.  While you twist those songs, you run around in a circle; this way, the mob is always chasing you around but not getting close enough to hit.  Meanwhile, you dot it to death.  AOE kiting is much the same, except that you dot a group of mobs instead of just one.  Not for the faint of heart. <img border="0" src="/shared/smilies/smile.gif" />  You can AOE kite at level 2 w/ Chords of Dissonance.  Fear kiting is just playing the fear song on a mob and beating it up, basically just like anyone else's fear kite, except that fear songs are AOE.  You can also kite with charm songs, but I haven't done that much, so you'll have to ask someone who has for more info.<br><br>Many instruments (including all the newbie ones you can get at bard guilds) are secondary only, which means you can't hold a weapon while playing them.  Instruments are like focus effects for bards: they increase the value of songs.  There are 4 different kinds of instruments (stringed, percussion, brass, wind), and each magnifies any song that is based on that type of instrument.  (Percussion instruments modify percussion based songs, etc.)  You can look up songs on this site to see which ones are based on what instrument.  (As far as I know, no instrument except for the epic modifies the singing skill.)  <br><br>A good site to visit (besides Allakhazam) for bard questions is www.eqdiva.com.  It's a bard only site with forums and other resources.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Lierta, 45 gnome mage<br>Attolia, 45 vah shir bard (EQ1)<br><br>Attolia, 19 wood elf rogue<br>Morganna, 16 dark elf druid <br>Oggok Server(EQ2)<br></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >0 Replies</td></tr></table>
